  "corelog_mapping_note": "DCID-7 has 7 classes; CoreLog's lithology enum has 6 (granite, basalt, sandstone, limestone, schist, ore). Each real patch keeps its true DCID label (dcid_class) AND a litho_label mapping to the nearest CoreLog class, used as the accuracy truth. The three clastic fines (siltstone, mudstone) and the red/light sandstones map to sandstone; marble (metamorphosed carbonate) maps to limestone; granite and basalt are exact. schist and ore have no real counterpart in DCID-7.",
  "honesty": "The lithology-CNN and core-ood models were trained on CoreLog's SYNTHETIC procedural core generator. Running them on these real DCID photographs is out-of-distribution: class predictions are indicative only, and the novelty (OOD) detector firing on most real patches is correct behaviour, not a bug.",
